<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 4:46PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southern Pulaski, west central Floyd, Wythe, central Carroll and
southwestern Montgomery Counties through 515 PM EDT...
At 446 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Favonia, or near Wytheville, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Pulaski...
Wytheville...
Hillsville...
Rural Retreat...
Max Meadows...
Allisonia...
and Indian Valley.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
